Definition 3.3 An endofunctor $F:\rm\underline{\underline{A}}\longrightarrow\rm\underline{\underline{A}}$ is said to be quasi-endofunctor if (GP1) $F$ is left SP-exact. (GP2) ${\rm Ext}(X,FQ)=0$, for any $X\in SGP(\rm\underline{\underline{A}})$ and $Q$ projective object of $\rm\underline{\underline{A}}$.
Definition 3.10 An object is Gorenstein projective (resp., injective) if, and only if, it is a direct summand of a Strongly Gorenstein projective (resp., injective) object.
Definition 3.1 An object of a category $\rm\underline{\underline{A}}$ is called $SP$(resp., $SI$)-object if it admits an exact sequence of the form $0\longrightarrow X\longrightarrow P\longrightarrow X\longrightarrow 0$ (resp., $0\longrightarrow X\longrightarrow I\longrightarrow X\longrightarrow 0$), with $P$ (resp., $I$) a projective (resp injective) object of $\rm\underline{\underline{A}}$. The class of $SP$ (resp., $SI$) objects is denoted $\underline{\underline{SP}}$ (resp., $\underline{\underline{SI}}$). We say that an endofunctor $F$ of $\rm\underline{\underline{A}}$ is $SP$-left (resp., right) exact if $0\longrightarrow FX\longrightarrow FP\longrightarrow FX$ (resp., $FX\longrightarrow FI\longrightarrow FX\longrightarrow 0$) is still exact.
Definition 4.1 [Holm, Definition 2.8] The Gorenstein projective dimension, $Gpd_{R}M$, of an $R-$module $M$ is defined by declaring that $Gpd_{R}M\leq n$ $(n\in\mathbb{N}_{0})$ if, and only if, $M$ has a Gorenstein projective resolution of length $n$. Similarly, one defines the Gorenstein injective dimension.
Definition 3.7 We say that an object $X$ in $\rm\underline{\underline{A}}$ is strongly Gorenstein injective or simply $SGI(\rm\underline{\underline{A}})$, if $X$ is $\underline{\underline{SI}}$ and for any injective object $Q$, the functor $hom(Q,-)$ is $SI-$exact for any injective object $Q$ in $\rm\underline{\underline{A}}$.
Definition 3.2 We say that an object $X$ in $\rm\underline{\underline{A}}$ is strongly Gorenstein projective noted $SGP(\rm\underline{\underline{A}})$ if $X$ is $SP$, such that the functor $hom(-,Q)$ is $SP-$ left exact for any projective object $Q$ in $\rm\underline{\underline{A}}$.
Definition 3.1. An extension ${N}$${G}$${H}$${k}$${e}$ is cosetal if for all $g,g^{\prime}\in G$ in which $e(g)=e(g^{\prime})$, there exists an $n\in N$ such that $k(n)g^{\prime}=g$.
Definition 4.9. Let ${N}$${G}$${H}$${k}$${e}$ be a cosetal extension and let $s$ be a section of $e$. Then an associated factor set is function $g_{s}\colon H\times H\to N$ for which $g_{s}(x,1)=1=g_{s}(1,x)$ and $g_{s}(h,h^{\prime})s(hh^{\prime})=s(h)s(h^{\prime})$ for all $h,h^{\prime}\in H$.
Definition 4.17. A factor set $g\in\mathcal{F^{*}}(H,N,E,[\varphi])$ is an inner factor set if and only if for some identity preserving $t\colon H\to N$ we have $g=\delta t$ where $\delta t(h,h^{\prime})=\varphi(h,t(h^{\prime}))t(hh^{\prime})^{-1}t(h)$.
